WEBVTT

00:02.469 --> 00:03.303
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"NECESSARY ROUGHNESS"...</i>

00:04.604 --> 00:07.073
IT'S MY ONE-YEAR
ANNIVERSARY OF SOBRIETY.

00:07.107 --> 00:09.609
YOU KNOW, THAT MEANS THE KING
IS FREE TO SHWING AGAIN.

00:09.642 --> 00:12.278
TERRENCE.
SHEERA. I'M A MODEL.

00:12.312 --> 00:13.446
ARE YOU HAPPY HERE?

00:13.480 --> 00:15.215
I'M HAPPIER<i>NOW.</i>

00:15.248 --> 00:16.649
YOU SUGGESTED
WE HACK INTO THEIR SYSTEM.

00:16.683 --> 00:17.550
I DIDN'T THINK
WE'D PULL IT OFF.

00:17.584 --> 00:20.487
INSTEAD OF HAVING ONE MAN
ON THE INSIDE,

00:20.520 --> 00:22.222
NOW WE HAVE TWO.

00:22.255 --> 00:24.124
Paloma: MR. CARELES --
HE'S OPAQUE TO MOST

00:24.157 --> 00:27.260
BUT TRANSPARENT
WHEN HE LOOKS AT YOU.

00:29.129 --> 00:30.463
HEY, I GOT A PROPOSITION
FOR YOU.

00:30.497 --> 00:31.598
COME TO IDAHO WITH US.

00:31.631 --> 00:34.100
I GOT TO MAKE SOME GOOFY SPEECH.
WHEELS UP IN FOUR HOURS.

00:37.470 --> 00:38.571
* COME ON

00:38.605 --> 00:40.473
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

00:40.507 --> 00:43.343
SO, SUN VALLEY?
AMAZING?

00:43.376 --> 00:45.478
IT WAS.
I MADE A LOT OF GREAT CONTACTS.

00:45.512 --> 00:47.213
OOH, TELL.

00:47.247 --> 00:50.583
WELL, I MET THE GOOGLE GUYS
AND THE YouTube GUYS

00:50.617 --> 00:52.452
AND THE GUY
THAT INVENTED THE SEGWAY.

00:52.485 --> 00:55.321
COOL. UM,
ANY OTHER "CONTACTS"?

00:55.355 --> 00:57.891
OH, GOD. WHAT ARE YOU,
PIMPING OR ASSISTING?

00:57.924 --> 01:00.393
I'M ASSISTING YOU...
TO A LITTLE FUN.

01:00.427 --> 01:03.196
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
I AM TOTALLY CAPABLE OF FUN.

01:03.229 --> 01:04.464
I HAVE TONS OF IT.

01:04.497 --> 01:07.334
OKAY, I DO YOUR CALENDAR, AND
SINCE YOU'VE STARTED THIS JOB,

01:07.367 --> 01:11.705
ALL I SEE IS TONS OF EMPTY SPACE
ON TONS OF NIGHTS.

01:11.738 --> 01:15.375
RIGHT. WELL, THAT CALENDAR
IS NOT ACCURATE COMPLETELY.

01:15.408 --> 01:18.211
MM.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
WHAT ARE YOU TYPING?

01:18.244 --> 01:21.181
G.N.O. --
V3 GIRLS NIGHT OUT.

01:21.214 --> 01:22.882
AGENTS, ASSISTANTS.
GIRLS ONLY.

01:22.916 --> 01:25.218
YOU SHOULD COME...
IF YOU'RE FREE.

01:25.251 --> 01:28.254
HOW ABOUT WE FOCUS ON
TODAY'S CALENDAR.

01:28.288 --> 01:29.356
THIS MORNING.

01:29.389 --> 01:30.490
NOLAN POWERS.

01:30.523 --> 01:31.725
THE SELF-HELP GURU?

01:31.758 --> 01:33.226
ONE IN THE SAME.

01:33.259 --> 01:34.527
BUT ACCORDING TO HIS BOOKS,

01:34.561 --> 01:36.463
HE DOESN'T EVEN
BELIEVE IN THERAPY.

01:36.496 --> 01:38.264
AND CONNOR
IS SENDING HIM TO ME?

01:38.298 --> 01:41.634
NO, CONNOR IS SENDING
<i>YOU</i>TO<i>HIM.</i>

01:43.236 --> 01:45.405
Powers: SNAP OUT OF IT.

01:45.438 --> 01:49.642
"PATHS TO POWER"...
IS ABOUT BELIEVING IN YOURSELF.

01:49.676 --> 01:52.212
NEVER SAY, "I CAN'T."

01:52.245 --> 01:55.415
THE POWER LIES IN YOU

01:55.448 --> 01:59.486
TO SHAPE AND MOLD AND BEND
YOUR DESTINY TO YOUR WILL.

01:59.519 --> 02:02.489
YOU SEE, WE FOCUS TOO MUCH
ON OUR WEAKNESSES.

02:02.522 --> 02:05.358
THAT'S WHY I JUST SAY NO
TO THERAPY.

02:05.392 --> 02:08.495
THERE'S TOO MUCH TALK
AND NOT ENOUGH ACTION.

02:08.528 --> 02:11.464
YOU TALK AND YOU TALK UNTIL
YOU MAKE YOUR<i>THERAPIST</i>WEALTHY.

02:11.498 --> 02:12.565
[ LAUGHTER ]

02:12.599 --> 02:15.502
YOU SEE, THERAPY, TO ME,
IS LIKE THE PRISON INDUSTRY.

02:15.535 --> 02:17.404
IT'S A LIFE SENTENCE.

02:17.437 --> 02:19.939
I GUESS YOU WON'T BE BUYING
<i>HIS</i>BOOK ANYTIME SOON.

02:19.973 --> 02:22.575
NOT UNLESS
I RUN OUT OF FIREWOOD.

02:22.609 --> 02:25.545
I, LIKE MANY OF YOU,
SUFFERED ABUSE AS A CHILD.

02:25.578 --> 02:29.416
PITIFULLY PLUMP --
I WAS RIDICULED.

02:29.449 --> 02:33.553
I USED TO BINGE ON PIZZAS
AND HOT DOGS AND CUPCAKES,

02:33.586 --> 02:36.222
AND THEN PIZZAS WITH HOT DOGS
AND CUPCAKES FOR TOPPINGS.

02:36.256 --> 02:37.991
[ LAUGHTER ]

02:38.024 --> 02:41.561
I COULDN'T SEE MY FEET,
BUT I'D WHINE --

02:41.594 --> 02:45.565
"WHY CAN'T I GET A GIRLFRIEND?
WHY CAN'T I GET A JOB?"

02:45.598 --> 02:49.703
I HAD TO WIPE THAT SAUCE
FROM MY EYES,

02:49.736 --> 02:52.272
TAKE A GOOD,
HARD LOOK IN THE MIRROR.

02:52.305 --> 02:54.441
I HAD TO DESTROY
THOSE WEAKNESSES,

02:54.474 --> 02:57.777
IGNORE THOSE VOICES, AND...
SNAP OUT OF IT.

02:57.811 --> 02:59.612
COME ON, NOW.
DON'T BE SHY.

02:59.646 --> 03:01.715
IGNORE THOSE VOICES AND --
WHAT IS IT?

03:01.748 --> 03:03.650
All: SNAP OUT OF IT!

03:03.683 --> 03:06.753
Powers: ONE MORE TIME.
I COULDN'T QUITE HEAR YOU.

03:06.786 --> 03:09.723
All: SNAP OUT OF IT!
WHOO!

03:09.756 --> 03:11.725
[ APPLAUSE ]
THANK YOU, EVERYBODY.

03:11.758 --> 03:14.227
NOLAN POWERS!
GREAT JOB!

03:17.364 --> 03:19.466
[ LAUGHS ]
YOU WANT SOME?
COME GET SOME.

03:19.499 --> 03:21.601
WHAT -- OH, NO, NO, NO!
[ Laughing ] OH, MY GOD.

03:21.634 --> 03:24.804
YOU ARE WAY STRONGER
THAN YOU LOOK.

03:24.838 --> 03:27.807
MM, POOR BABY.
YOU WANT ME TO STOP?

03:27.841 --> 03:29.442
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:29.476 --> 03:31.044
MM.

03:31.077 --> 03:32.746
* PIECES OF YOU ON THE GROUND

03:32.779 --> 03:33.780
OHH!

03:33.813 --> 03:35.281
[ THUD ]

03:35.315 --> 03:37.350
[ LAUGHS ]

03:37.384 --> 03:38.351
[ GRUNTS ]

03:38.385 --> 03:39.619
I HOPE
YOU'RE NOT A SPRINTER.

03:39.652 --> 03:42.856
OH, GIRL,
I AM A MARATHON MAN.

03:42.889 --> 03:46.493
* I PULL THE TRIGGER, RUN AWAY

03:46.526 --> 03:48.695
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]
* RUN AWAY

03:48.728 --> 03:50.630
* HEY

03:50.663 --> 03:52.499
* TRIGGER ME

03:52.532 --> 03:55.869
* OOH, YOU DON'T HAVE TO
STAY HERE ANYMORE *

03:55.902 --> 03:57.303
* SOMEONE CLOSE THE DOOR
BEHIND YOU WHEN YOU LEAVE *

03:57.337 --> 03:59.706
HEY, MAN.
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

03:59.739 --> 04:02.842
AH, THERE HE IS.
THE MOSES OF MOTIVATION.

04:02.876 --> 04:04.511
HA! I'M STEALING THAT,
McCLANE.

04:04.544 --> 04:06.379
[ CHUCKLES ]
GREAT SPEECH OUT THERE.

04:06.413 --> 04:07.514
I'D LIKE TO INTRODUCE YOU GUYS
TO SOMEONE.

04:07.547 --> 04:10.650
ALLIE, NOLAN,
THIS IS DR. DANI SANTINO.

04:10.684 --> 04:12.085
SHE'S OUR
IN-HOUSE THERAPIST.

04:12.118 --> 04:15.088
NICE TO MEET YOU,
DR. SANTINO.
AND YOU, MR. POWERS.

04:15.121 --> 04:16.456
MY FIANCÃ©E, ALLIE.

04:16.489 --> 04:18.591
SO, THERAPIST, HUH?

04:18.625 --> 04:21.428
LET ME HAZARD A GUESS.
YOU'RE NOT A FAN OF MY WORK.

04:21.461 --> 04:23.797
OH, LET'S SAY THAT
I'M AWARE OF YOUR WORK.

04:23.830 --> 04:25.665
AH, THE CURSE OF INDIFFERENCE.
YOU WOUND ME.

04:25.699 --> 04:28.535
OH, I'M JUST SURPRISED
THAT YOU'RE SO ANTI-THERAPY

04:28.568 --> 04:31.805
WHEN MANY OF "POWERS PILLARS"
HAVE THERAPEUTIC ROOTS.

04:31.838 --> 04:34.441
I'M NOT ANTI-THERAPY.
I'M PRO-ACTIVE.

04:34.474 --> 04:36.676
I PREFER NOT TO DWELL
ON THE PAST.
OH, I DON'T DWELL ON IT.

04:36.710 --> 04:39.546
I HELP PEOPLE COME TO TERMS WITH
IT SO THEY CAN MOVE FORWARD.

04:39.579 --> 04:42.449
WHAT'S THE EXPRESSION?
"TALK IS CHEAP"?

04:42.482 --> 04:44.684
EXCEPT THERAPY,
WHERE TALK IS EXPENSIVE,

04:44.718 --> 04:46.853
TAKES YEARS, GOES IN CIRCLES
WITH NO PROGRESS.

04:46.886 --> 04:48.722
WOW, YOU NEED
A BETTER THERAPIST.

04:48.755 --> 04:50.490
I'VE NEVER HAD ONE,
ACTUALLY.

04:50.523 --> 04:53.360
LET ME REFER TO YOU ONE.
ALL RIGHT.
STOP. DING, DING, DING.

04:53.393 --> 04:54.694
EVERYONE BACK TO
THEIR OWN CORNERS.

04:54.728 --> 04:57.564
I WANT EVERYONE TO GET ALONG
HERE IN THE V3 SANDBOX.

04:57.597 --> 04:59.699
ALLIE, MAY I BORROW
YOUR SOON-TO-BE HUSBAND?

04:59.733 --> 05:01.534
WE WANT TO TALK
ABOUT SOME BOOK DETAILS.

05:01.568 --> 05:02.702
PLEASE.

05:02.736 --> 05:03.837
OKAY. COME ON.

05:03.870 --> 05:05.805
PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

05:08.441 --> 05:10.877
SORRY.
NOLAN CAN BE OPINIONATED.

05:10.910 --> 05:12.645
MOST GREAT MINDS ARE.

05:12.679 --> 05:14.414
[ LAUGHS ]
YOU'RE KIND.

05:14.447 --> 05:16.516
MM.

05:18.518 --> 05:19.619
T.K.: YOU ARE A BEAST!

05:19.652 --> 05:23.823
OH, BUT I'M A LION TAMER.
SIEGFRIED AND ROY IN THIS...

05:23.857 --> 05:25.592
SHEERA?

05:25.625 --> 05:28.428
SHEERA?

05:37.537 --> 05:40.640
DID I JUST GET JETERED
IN MY OWN HOME?

05:40.674 --> 05:41.975
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

05:42.008 --> 05:43.743
DR. SANTINO.
YES?

05:43.777 --> 05:45.412
SAM CONTE
FROM THE L.A. OFFICE.

05:45.445 --> 05:46.680
I'M CINDY LUCK'S
WEST COAST REP.

05:46.713 --> 05:47.947
OH, PLEASURE.

05:47.981 --> 05:50.750
IS ALL MINE. CINDY'S
DOING GREAT, SO THANK YOU.

05:50.784 --> 05:53.186
WELL, I GUESS THERAPY WORKS
FOR SOME PEOPLE.

05:53.219 --> 05:54.054
[ LAUGHS ]

05:54.087 --> 05:55.922
I'M A BIG FAN OF
THERAPISTS, MYSELF.

05:57.657 --> 05:59.859
LISTEN, I GOT A MEETING
TO GET TO,

05:59.893 --> 06:02.996
BUT MAYBE OUR PATHS
WILL CROSS AGAIN WHILE I'M HERE.

06:03.029 --> 06:04.631
MAYBE.

06:09.769 --> 06:11.771
[ INHALING DEEPLY ]

06:15.809 --> 06:17.977
MR. POWERS?

06:20.880 --> 06:24.484
NOLAN?

06:24.517 --> 06:26.553
YOO-HOO.
SNAP OUT OF IT.

06:29.956 --> 06:31.791
CAN I HELP YOU
WITH SOMETHING?

06:31.825 --> 06:33.993
DOES THIS WINDOW OPEN?

06:34.027 --> 06:37.030
WHAT? NO. WHY?

06:37.063 --> 06:40.200
'CAUSE
I WANT TO KILL MYSELF.

06:40.233 --> 06:43.737
* BABY, WORK YOUR MAGIC ON ME

06:58.685 --> 07:00.520
NOLAN.

07:04.657 --> 07:08.328
NOLAN,
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

07:12.198 --> 07:13.633
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH,
DOOR OPENS ]

07:13.667 --> 07:14.701
Allie: THERE YOU ARE.

07:14.734 --> 07:16.670
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER.

07:16.703 --> 07:18.672
YOU FINISHED WITH CONNOR?
HEY, HON.

07:18.705 --> 07:20.507
I'M SORRY.
I GOT A MIGRAINE KICKING IN.

07:20.540 --> 07:22.575
I NEEDED
SOME QUIET SPACE.

07:22.609 --> 07:24.577
AWW.
HE GETS THOSE A LOT.

07:24.611 --> 07:26.613
CAN'T DO ANYTHING
BUT NAP OUT OF IT.

07:26.646 --> 07:29.149
COME ON.
LET'S GET SOME FUEL IN YOU.

07:29.182 --> 07:31.518
CARE TO JOIN US
FOR LUNCH?

07:31.551 --> 07:34.521
UH, WHAT? NO.
BUT THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

07:34.554 --> 07:37.123
DR. SANTINO.

07:40.093 --> 07:43.630
Nico:
YOU'RE PUSHING YOUR LUCK.

07:43.663 --> 07:45.765
Bennett: THE GOVERNMENT'S LUCK
IS INFINITE.

07:45.799 --> 07:48.535
CORNERED THE MARKET
ON RABBIT FEET.

07:48.568 --> 07:50.637
OUR HACKER IS INSIDE
V3 SECURE NETWORK.

07:50.670 --> 07:52.539
JUST LET HIM DO HIS THING.

07:52.572 --> 07:55.108
TROY CUTLER IS OUT OF TOWN
ON BUSINESS FOR 24 HOURS.

07:55.141 --> 07:57.043
NOW IS THE TIME.

07:57.077 --> 07:59.079
I NEED HARD COPIES.
OTHERWISE, IT'S NOT ADMISSIBLE.

07:59.112 --> 08:00.680
IT'S STILL RISKY.

08:00.714 --> 08:02.215
AND MY NECK'S
ON THE CHOPPING BLOCK.

08:02.248 --> 08:03.983
AND YOU'RE NECK DEEP --

08:04.017 --> 08:06.586
WIRETAPS, BRIBERY, AND A HOST
OF OTHER ILLEGAL ACTIVITIES

08:06.619 --> 08:09.022
YOU PERFORMED FOR YOUR OLD PAL
MARSHALL PITTMAN.

08:09.055 --> 08:12.058
WHICH YOU'RE WIPING CLEAN,
AS PART OF OUR DEAL.

08:12.092 --> 08:15.628
YES.
BUT RISK IS PART AND PARCEL.

08:17.330 --> 08:20.633
YOU GIVE A FED AN INCH,
HE'LL TAKE A MILE.

08:20.667 --> 08:23.703
BUT IN THIS CASE,
YOU'RE GONNA MEET ME HALFWAY.

08:23.737 --> 08:25.238
MEANING?

08:25.271 --> 08:28.808
I'LL DO THIS...
BUT I WANT A FAVOR IN RETURN.

08:30.310 --> 08:33.146
CALL IT A DOWN PAYMENT.

08:38.251 --> 08:40.620
NO, NO, NO. YOU -- YOU -- YOU
HAVE REALLY OUTDONE YOURSELF.

08:40.653 --> 08:43.189
THIS EPISODE 7 --
BEST ONE YET.

08:43.223 --> 08:46.192
DON'T TELL LUCAS I SAID THAT.
ALL RIGHT.

08:46.226 --> 08:49.129
NO, MAY THE FORCE
BE WITH<i>YOU,</i>J.J. SEE YOU.

08:49.162 --> 08:51.297
SANTINO.

08:51.331 --> 08:54.200
[ As Yoda ]
DO FOR YOU, WHAT CAN I?
WHAT'S THAT?

08:54.234 --> 08:56.136
[ Normal voice ] YODA.
OH.

08:56.169 --> 08:58.805
I, UH -- OKAY.
I GOT TO ASK YOU SOMETHING.

08:58.838 --> 09:02.142
NOLAN POWERS -- HOW WELL
DO YOU KNOW HIM EXACTLY?

09:02.175 --> 09:03.710
I KNOW HIM WELL.

09:03.743 --> 09:06.746
I MEAN, BEEN A FRIEND,
CLIENT FOR 15 YEARS.

09:06.780 --> 09:09.182
HE'S A LITTLE QUIRKY,
UNPREDICTABLE.

09:09.215 --> 09:11.151
DON'T PLAY POKER WITH HIM,
'CAUSE HE'LL MOTIVATE YOUR
MONEY RIGHT OUT OF YOU.

09:11.184 --> 09:12.852
WHY DO YOU ASK?

09:12.886 --> 09:17.157
HE SAID SOMETHING TO ME TODAY
THAT WAS...DISCONCERTING.

09:17.190 --> 09:19.125
DID HE HIT ON YOU?

09:19.159 --> 09:21.394
[ SIGHS ]

09:21.428 --> 09:23.863
HE TOLD ME THAT
HE WANTS TO KILL HIMSELF.

09:23.897 --> 09:26.733
POWERS?! NO.

09:26.766 --> 09:29.169
HE MUST HAVE BEEN
MAKING A JOKE.

09:29.202 --> 09:33.406
IT WASN'T SEINFELD TELLING ME.
IT SEEMED PRETTY SERIOUS.

09:33.440 --> 09:34.741
YES, HE'S UNDER PRESSURE.

09:34.774 --> 09:36.876
HE'S GOT A BOOK TOUR,
A NEW TV SHOW.

09:36.910 --> 09:38.778
BUT SUICIDE? NO. NEVER.

09:38.812 --> 09:41.781
I KNOW WHAT I SAW,
AND I KNOW WHAT I HEARD.

09:41.815 --> 09:46.186
THIS ISN'T ABOUT
THIS LITTLE THERAPY FEUD

09:46.219 --> 09:47.420
YOU GUYS HAVE GOING,
IS IT?

09:47.454 --> 09:49.789
I-I'M SORRY.

09:49.823 --> 09:52.692
YOU THINK I'M MAKING THIS UP
BECAUSE POWERS AND I DISAGREE?

09:52.726 --> 09:56.863
WOW.
OKAY. EXCUSE ME.

09:56.896 --> 09:58.732
COME ON, SANTINO.
I DIDN'T MEAN IT LIKE THAT.

09:58.765 --> 10:01.401
YOU WANT ME TO BACK OFF,
THAT'S TOTALLY FINE, OKAY?

10:01.434 --> 10:05.138
HE'S YOUR FRIEND,
NOT MINE.

10:05.171 --> 10:06.840
DID WE JUST HAVE
OUR FIRST FIGHT?

10:09.909 --> 10:12.746
Man: 1, 2, 3, 4...
* IT'S HOW YOU MOVE YOUR HIPS

10:12.779 --> 10:16.282
...5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10.
* SHAKE IT ALL AROUND

10:16.316 --> 10:19.919
JACKS -- 1, 2, 3, 4...
* I WANT TO KISS YOUR LIPS

10:19.953 --> 10:23.323
...5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10.
* JUST LIKE HONEY DRIPS

10:23.356 --> 10:24.324
* NOT MOVE TOO FAST

10:24.357 --> 10:26.092
RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT!

10:26.126 --> 10:28.361
AND 3...
* WE'RE GONNA TAKE OUR TIME

10:28.395 --> 10:32.365
...4...5...6...7.
* NOT MOVE TOO FAST

10:32.399 --> 10:34.300
* WE'RE GONNA TAKE OUR TIME

10:34.334 --> 10:35.769
HEY, YOU.

10:35.802 --> 10:37.303
DON'T "HEY YOU" ME.
YOU JETERED ME?

10:37.337 --> 10:39.239
I JETERED YOU?

10:39.272 --> 10:40.373
DEREK JETER --

10:40.407 --> 10:42.842
THE MASTER OF THE FRIENDLY
ONE-NIGHT-STAND GIFT BAG.

10:42.876 --> 10:44.310
"DON'T GO AWAY MAD,
JUST GO AWAY."

10:44.344 --> 10:46.913
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.
I DON'T GET JETERED.

10:46.946 --> 10:47.881
I JETER PEOPLE.

10:47.914 --> 10:50.383
AH, SO, YOU'RE MAD
YOU DIDN'T JETER ME FIRST.

10:50.417 --> 10:53.720
THAT THE JETERER
BECAME THE JETEREE?

10:53.753 --> 10:55.955
YOU'RE TWISTING MY WORDS,
SHEERA.

10:55.989 --> 10:58.858
OKAY, WHAT'S THE PROBLEM, T.K.?
WE BOTH GOT WHAT WE WANTED.

10:58.892 --> 11:01.161
NO STRINGS ATTACHED,
NO HARD FEELINGS.

11:01.194 --> 11:03.263
JUST MOVE ON.
LISTEN, I JUST --

11:03.296 --> 11:04.864
COULD YOU --

11:04.898 --> 11:06.766
COULD YOU PLEASE JUST STOP
PUNCHING FOR ONE SECOND.

11:06.800 --> 11:07.701
* TILL I CAN TAKE IT NO MORE

11:07.734 --> 11:10.403
MAYBE I WANTED YOU TO STAY
FOR BREAKFAST.

11:10.437 --> 11:11.871
ATTACH MORE STRINGS.

11:11.905 --> 11:14.174
UNTIL YOU SNIPPED THEM?

11:14.207 --> 11:18.178
[ SIGHS ]
* THE WAY YOU MOVE YOUR HIPS

11:18.211 --> 11:22.882
OKAY, LOOK, HEY.
MAYBE I FELT SOMETHING, TOO.

11:22.916 --> 11:24.884
MAYBE I WANTED
TO STAY FOR BREAKFAST

11:24.918 --> 11:27.187
AND THE REST OF THE WEEK.

11:27.220 --> 11:31.191
SO, MAYBE...
I LEFT YOU A CLUE,

11:31.224 --> 11:34.427
A FREE PASS TO THE ONE PLACE
I FREQUENT MOST,

11:34.461 --> 11:37.997
SO IF WHAT I FELT
WAS REAL AND YOU WANTED ME,

11:38.031 --> 11:41.801
IF YOU WANTED TO TAKE
THOSE STRINGS AND TIE ME UP,

11:41.835 --> 11:44.471
MAYBE YOU'D KNOW
JUST WHERE TO FIND ME.

11:44.504 --> 11:45.939
* C-C-C-C-COME ON AND SHAKE IT

11:45.972 --> 11:47.807
WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT THAT?

11:47.841 --> 11:50.844
* C-C-C-C-COME ON AND SHAKE IT

11:50.877 --> 11:52.345
* SH-SH-SH-SHAKE IT
HMM?

11:52.379 --> 11:56.850
* SHAKE IT ALL NIGHT LONG

11:56.883 --> 11:59.519
* 'CAUSE I'M YOUR BOYFRIEND,
BABY *

11:59.552 --> 12:02.555
CAN YOU STAY
FOR BREAKFAST?

12:02.589 --> 12:05.425
NO.
I WANT TO STAY FOR LUNCH.

12:05.458 --> 12:08.294
MM, I COULD GET USED TO
THAT MEAL PLAN.

12:08.328 --> 12:09.429
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

12:09.462 --> 12:11.464
* COME ON, SHAKE IT, NOW

12:18.438 --> 12:20.473
Connor: ALL RIGHT,
I WANT TO POUND IT.

12:20.507 --> 12:24.210
WE HAVE A BOOK SIGNING MONDAY,
WHICH LAUNCHES A 60-CITY TOUR.

12:24.244 --> 12:26.513
OF COURSE, NEXT WEEK, WE HAVE
"LETTERMAN," THE "TODAY" SHOW,

12:26.546 --> 12:28.581
"TONIGHT SHOW."

12:28.615 --> 12:30.884
"CELEBRITY APPRENTICE" --
HE'S A JUDGE DURING SWEEPS.

12:30.917 --> 12:32.018
I LIKE THAT.

12:32.052 --> 12:33.053
AND THEN, OF COURSE,

12:33.086 --> 12:36.423
THE PREMIERE OF
"POWER UP WITH NOLAN POWERS."

12:36.456 --> 12:37.891
THE WORLD IS YOURS,
MY FRIEND.

12:37.924 --> 12:39.426
GREAT JOB, EVERYBODY.
AWESOME JOB.

12:39.459 --> 12:41.061
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

12:41.094 --> 12:44.364
THAT'S JUST AWESOME.
THANK YOU SO MUCH. AWESOME.

12:44.397 --> 12:46.533
GOOD JOB.
GREAT JOB. THANK YOU.
GOOD JOB. ALL RIGHT.

12:46.566 --> 12:48.868
LOOK AT THIS ANSWER MAN.

12:48.902 --> 12:51.438
[ LAUGHS ]
YOU CALLED IT.

12:51.471 --> 12:53.406
YOU SAID IT WOULD HAPPEN
AND LOOK AT WHAT WE'VE BUILT.

12:53.440 --> 12:54.908
PILLAR NUMBER FOUR --

12:54.941 --> 12:57.010
BELIEVE IT,
AND YOU CAN ACHIEVE IT.

12:57.043 --> 13:00.547
THAT'S RIGHT. HEY.
HOW YOU FEELING? YOU OKAY?

13:00.580 --> 13:03.850
TOP OF THE WORLD, MAC.
WHY?

13:03.883 --> 13:06.319
WELL, DR. SANTINO
SHOWED A LITTLE CONCERN

13:06.353 --> 13:08.321
OVER A CONVERSATION
THAT YOU GUYS HAD TOGETHER.

13:08.355 --> 13:09.522
RIGHT.

13:09.556 --> 13:12.625
I HAD A MIGRAINE, SO I DUCKED IN
AN OFFICE FOR SOME QUIET.

13:12.659 --> 13:15.328
I HAD NO IDEA I WAS TRESPASSING
ON HER PROPERTY.

13:15.362 --> 13:18.932
OKAY. SO, YOU DIDN'T SAY THAT
YOU WANTED TO KILL YOURSELF?

13:18.965 --> 13:19.866
YOU EVER HAVE A MIGRAINE?

13:19.899 --> 13:22.035
YOU'D WANT TO KILL YOURSELF,
TOO. I'M FINE.

13:22.068 --> 13:23.536
LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA DENY
THERE'S SOME PRESSURE

13:23.570 --> 13:26.272
WITH THIS BOOK LAUNCH,
THIS SHOW.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.541
BUT I'M FINE, MAC,
I SWEAR.

13:28.575 --> 13:29.976
OKAY.
COME ON.

13:30.010 --> 13:32.412
NOW, HOW ABOUT SOME SUSHI?
I'M BUYING.

13:32.445 --> 13:35.882
OKAY.

13:35.915 --> 13:37.884
SO, WE'RE ALL TWISTY AND TURNY.
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

13:37.917 --> 13:39.552
LIKE, WE'RE, LIKE, BASICALLY --
AH, AH, HEY, HEY!

13:39.586 --> 13:42.555
I DON'T NEED THE VISUAL.
I WANT TO<i>HEAR</i>ABOUT HER.

13:42.589 --> 13:45.658
SHE'S SUPER HOT.
SHE'S FUNNY.

13:45.692 --> 13:47.994
LIKE ME WITH A SOFTER BOOTY.
[ LAUGHS ]

13:48.028 --> 13:49.996
HA HA HA.
SO, WHAT'S THE "BUT"?

13:50.030 --> 13:52.365
THE "BUT" WITH ONE "T,"
NOT TWO.

13:52.399 --> 13:54.067
OH, NO BUTs.

13:54.100 --> 13:56.603
I'M GETTING IT.
I'M LOVING IT. HUH!

13:56.636 --> 13:58.338
DOC, YOU EVER HAD ANY
THAT WAS SO GOOD

13:58.371 --> 14:00.907
THAT YOU JUST WANT TO
TELL THE WORLD ABOUT IT?

14:00.940 --> 14:04.044
I AM SO HAPPY FOR YOU.

14:06.046 --> 14:08.481
MAY I MAKE A DIAGNOSIS,
GOOD DOCTOR?

14:10.483 --> 14:12.552
I THINK THAT YOU
NEED TO GET SOME.
OH, TERRENCE!

14:12.585 --> 14:14.554
I DO. I MEAN, IT'S WRITTEN
ALL OVER YOUR FACE.

14:14.587 --> 14:15.955
KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

14:15.989 --> 14:19.059
I COULD ONLY SAY THAT
FROM PERSONAL EXPERIENCE
OF LOOKING IN THE MIRROR

14:19.092 --> 14:20.593
AND SEEING
THAT DEPLETED LOOK, OKAY?

14:20.627 --> 14:21.661
SO,
WHAT I'M SAYING IS...

14:21.695 --> 14:23.997
MAYBE THERE'S SOMEBODY
AT THE HAWKS ORGANIZATION

14:24.030 --> 14:25.365
WHO'S ALWAYS
HAD A CRUSH ON YOU.

14:25.398 --> 14:26.700
AT THE HAWKS?

14:26.733 --> 14:28.968
MM-HMM.
MY BOY REGGIE!

14:29.002 --> 14:30.970
HE'S A GOOD DUDE.
I CAN HOOK Y'ALL UP.
NO.

14:31.004 --> 14:32.939
I MEAN, I'M SURE
HE'S A "GOOD DUDE."

14:32.972 --> 14:35.408
BUT THANK YOU.
I'M SET.

14:35.442 --> 14:36.543
YOU SURE?

14:36.576 --> 14:37.944
YEAH.

14:37.977 --> 14:39.045
WELL, OKAY.
SUIT YOURSELF.

14:39.079 --> 14:40.580
BUT, YOU KNOW,
WORK HARD, PLAY HARD.

14:40.613 --> 14:41.681
GOT TO MAKE TIME FOR THE...
[ GRUNTING ]

14:41.715 --> 14:43.016
OH, STOP IT!

14:43.049 --> 14:44.718
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
MY BAD. YEAH, I --

14:44.751 --> 14:46.953
OKAY.
WELL, YOU DO YOU.

14:46.986 --> 14:48.154
YOU DO YOU.
YOU DO YOU.

14:48.188 --> 14:49.089
BUH-BYE.

14:55.095 --> 14:57.630
* ON THE FLOOR,
ON THE FLOOR *

14:57.664 --> 14:59.966
* ON THE FLOOR,
ON THE FLOOR *

15:00.000 --> 15:01.501
* ON THE FLOOR,
ON THE FLOOR *

15:01.534 --> 15:04.671
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

15:07.774 --> 15:09.509
SO,
LOGAN IS A CUTE JERK.

15:09.542 --> 15:12.712
AND NOAH
ONLY WEARS TIGHT PANTS.

15:12.746 --> 15:14.047
SO YOU'LL LOOK
AT HIS BULGE.

15:14.080 --> 15:15.048
[ LAUGHTER ]
Woman: EXACTLY.

15:15.081 --> 15:19.185
AND THEN THERE'S TROY.
WHO'S AN ACQUIRED TASTE.

15:19.219 --> 15:22.088
YEAH, IF YOU LIKE...HAGGIS.
[ LAUGHTER ]

15:22.122 --> 15:26.426
TROY IS DEFINITELY HAGGIS.
HERE'S TO HAGGIS!

15:26.459 --> 15:28.128
[ LAUGHTER ]

15:28.161 --> 15:29.596
WHOO!

15:29.629 --> 15:31.731
IS THIS WOMEN ONLY
OR CAN ANYONE JOIN?

15:31.765 --> 15:34.668
OH, SAM, YOU CAME!
SIT!

15:34.701 --> 15:36.036
HOW YOU GUYS DOING?

15:36.069 --> 15:37.737
HELLO, AGAIN.
HELLO.

15:37.771 --> 15:40.507
I THOUGHT
THIS WAS G.N.O.?

15:40.540 --> 15:43.777
YEAH, WELL, PART OF G.N.O.
IS ABOUT MAKING CONTACTS.

15:43.810 --> 15:45.545
AT LEAST
LET ME BUY YOU A DRINK.

15:45.578 --> 15:47.180
I HAVE TWO.

15:47.213 --> 15:49.215
SO YOU DO.

15:49.249 --> 15:51.518
HMM.

15:51.551 --> 15:52.552
CONNOR RAVES ABOUT YOU.
YEAH?

15:52.585 --> 15:54.220
SO HOW DO I MAKE AN APPOINTMENT
ON YOUR COUCH?

15:54.254 --> 15:56.423
[ LAUGHS ]
WHY? WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

15:56.456 --> 15:58.425
I HAVE BEEN CRUSHING
REALLY HARD

15:58.458 --> 16:01.494
ON THIS DAZZLING,
ELECTRIC WOMAN.

16:01.528 --> 16:04.798
REALLY? SO, THEN,
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

16:04.831 --> 16:06.533
THE PROBLEM IS I'M SHY.

16:06.566 --> 16:07.701
[ LAUGHS ]

16:07.734 --> 16:09.536
SO, I SHOULD BE DIRECT
AND TELL HER

16:09.569 --> 16:10.804
EXACTLY WHAT I WANT
FROM HER?

16:10.837 --> 16:12.505
YOU COULD.

16:12.539 --> 16:15.475
BUT THEN WHO'S TO SAY
THAT SHE WON'T REJECT YOUR WANTS

16:15.508 --> 16:17.610
AND THEN REPORT YOU
TO H.R.?

16:17.644 --> 16:18.578
[ LAUGHS ]
SHE WOULDN'T DO THAT.

16:18.611 --> 16:19.713
MM.

16:19.746 --> 16:21.214
WOULD SHE?

16:21.247 --> 16:24.084
I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT KIND OF PERSON IS SHE?

16:24.117 --> 16:26.453
IMPRESSIVE, BEAUTIFUL...
UH-HUH.

16:26.486 --> 16:28.054
...AND SITTING
RIGHT NEXT TO ME.

16:29.756 --> 16:31.624
UH...

16:31.658 --> 16:34.494
WELL, NOT SO MUCH
WITH THE SHY.

16:34.527 --> 16:36.463
MNH-MNH.

16:36.496 --> 16:39.799
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

16:39.833 --> 16:41.534
AH, SAVED BY
THE VIBRATION.

16:41.568 --> 16:42.736
THIS IS DANI.

16:42.769 --> 16:47.073
WHAT?
I'M -- SLOW DOWN. WHAT?

16:47.107 --> 16:48.508
Allie: I DIDN'T KNOW
WHO ELSE TO CALL.

16:48.541 --> 16:50.610
I DIDN'T WANT TO CAUSE
A PANIC.

16:50.643 --> 16:53.113
ALLIE, IT'S OKAY.
SIT DOWN.

16:53.146 --> 16:56.216
EVERYTHING YOU SAY TO ME
IS CONFIDENTIAL.

16:56.249 --> 16:59.219
I COULDN'T IGNORE THIS.

16:59.252 --> 17:02.589
NOLAN IS VERY PRIVATE.

17:02.622 --> 17:05.859
HE CAN BE SECRETIVE.

17:05.892 --> 17:09.229
AT NIGHT,
HE STAYS UP FOR HOURS.

17:09.262 --> 17:12.866
IT'S LIKE HE DOESN'T
WANT TO BE NEAR ME.

17:12.899 --> 17:16.636
OH. COUPLES' THERAPY
IS NOT AN OPTION.

17:16.670 --> 17:19.773
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:19.806 --> 17:23.109
ANYWAY, UM...

17:23.143 --> 17:25.245
TONIGHT HE WENT OUT.

17:25.278 --> 17:29.149
AND HE LEFT
HIS LAPTOP OPEN.

17:29.182 --> 17:31.851
[ Voice breaking ]
AND WHEN I FOUND...

17:31.885 --> 17:34.688
WHAT HE'S BEEN DOING...

17:34.721 --> 17:37.157
I READ HIS E-MAILS.

17:37.190 --> 17:41.127
I WISH
I DIDN'T READ THEM.

17:41.161 --> 17:44.698
WHAT WAS
IN THE E-MAILS?

17:54.908 --> 17:57.277
[ SIGHS ]

17:59.946 --> 18:01.915
THREE HAD WEBISODES
FROM EACH DEPARTMENT.

18:01.948 --> 18:03.783
NOLAN POWERS --
WE HAVE TO TALK.

18:03.817 --> 18:06.386
SANTINO, YOU GOT TO GET OFF
THIS POWERS FIXATION.

18:06.419 --> 18:09.356
I MEAN, YES, THE GUY'S QUIRKY,
BUT GENIUS USUALLY IS.

18:09.389 --> 18:10.557
QUIRKY? MNH-MNH.

18:10.590 --> 18:14.394
QUIRK DOES NOT MAKE A GROWN MAN
SET UP A FAKE E-MAIL ACCOUNT

18:14.427 --> 18:16.763
SO THAT HE CAN HAVE IMPROPER
LATE-NIGHT DISCUSSIONS

18:16.796 --> 18:20.266
WITH 12-YEAR-OLD GIRLS...

18:20.300 --> 18:23.336
WHICH IS EXACTLY
WHAT POWERS IS DOING.

18:30.777 --> 18:31.711
I WOULD NEVER DO THAT!
NOT IN A MILLION YEARS!

18:33.847 --> 18:37.751
ALL RIGHT. BUT THE FAKE ACCOUNT?
THESE E-MAILS?

18:37.784 --> 18:40.754
I GET THOUSANDS A DAY
FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD.

18:40.787 --> 18:42.622
BUT I'VE NEVER SEEN THESE.

18:42.655 --> 18:45.225
AND WHY THE HELL WOULD I CREATE
A FAKE E-MAIL ACCOUNT

18:45.258 --> 18:48.294
TO TALK TO LITTLE GIRLS ABOUT
SpongeBob SquarePants OR --

18:48.328 --> 18:50.630
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT "A.N.T. FARM" IS!

18:50.663 --> 18:52.565
Dani:
WE ARE JUST TRYING TO HELP.

18:52.599 --> 18:53.933
IF YOU ARE STRUGGLING
WITH ANYTHING

18:53.967 --> 18:54.768
OR YOU NEED TO TALK...

18:54.801 --> 18:57.604
YOU KNOW,
I EXPECT THIS FROM HER.

18:57.637 --> 18:59.939
BUT YOU? AFTER EVERYTHING
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH,

18:59.973 --> 19:01.608
THIS IS HOW YOU TREAT ME?

19:01.641 --> 19:03.576
NOLAN, I'M ON YOUR SIDE,
BUT, COME ON, MAN.

19:03.610 --> 19:05.578
YOU GOT TO ADMIT THIS REQUIRES
SOME SORT OF EXPLANATION.

19:05.612 --> 19:08.314
NO, IT DOES NOT!
BECAUSE I DIDN'T DO THIS!

19:10.617 --> 19:13.920
NOLAN, YOU KNOW, ALLIE
IS VERY CONCERNED ABOUT YOU.

19:13.953 --> 19:18.525
SHE AND I ARE DONE.
SHE'S PACKING AS WE SPEAK.

19:18.558 --> 19:19.959
AND YOU'RE NEXT
IF YOU KEEP THIS UP.

19:19.993 --> 19:23.329
O-OKAY, LOOK.
NOLAN, PLEASE.

19:23.363 --> 19:26.332
FOR YOUR SAKE, HELP US
GET TO THE BOTTOM OF THIS.

19:26.366 --> 19:28.768
YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:28.802 --> 19:30.870
I'LL TAKE A LIE-DETECTOR TEST
RIGHT HERE TODAY.

19:30.904 --> 19:35.342
THAT WILL PROVE INDISPUTABLY
I DID NOT SEND THOSE E-MAILS.

19:36.810 --> 19:39.346
YOU SET IT UP.

19:41.781 --> 19:43.783
[ SIGHS ]

19:43.817 --> 19:46.653
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

19:46.686 --> 19:48.655
HMM. WELL, THAT'S ODD.

19:48.688 --> 19:51.891
WHY DID TROY INSTALL HIS OWN
SECURITY SYSTEM ON TOP OF V3's?

19:54.861 --> 19:56.796
FOLLOW MY LEAD.
WHAT?

19:56.830 --> 19:59.599
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
INSTALLING NEW ANTI-MALWARE

19:59.632 --> 20:01.267
JUST IN CASE
THERE'S ANOTHER SBG ATTACK.

20:01.301 --> 20:04.270
NO, NO. I MEAN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING RIGHT NOW?

20:04.304 --> 20:07.540
[ Laughing ] WAIT, TIME OUT.
WHAT?

20:07.574 --> 20:09.676
YEAH, I WAS A SPORTING-GOODS
MODEL FOR YEARS

20:09.709 --> 20:12.679
UNTIL I GOT DISCOVERED AND
I BECAME A HIGH-FASHION MODEL.

20:12.712 --> 20:13.747
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:13.780 --> 20:15.949
IT'S NOT LIKE IT WAS MY DREAM
TO BE A SEX OBJECT.

20:15.982 --> 20:18.585
BUT I CAN'T KNOCK IT.
IT PUT ME THROUGH COLLEGE.

20:18.618 --> 20:20.720
AND WHERE DID YOU GO?
THE UNIVERSITY OF HOTNESS?

20:20.754 --> 20:23.556
HA HA. NO, STANFORD.
[ LAUGHS ]

20:23.590 --> 20:25.825
WOW. BOY, THAT'S A --
THAT'S A GOOD SCHOOL.

20:25.859 --> 20:29.362
YEAH, I WAS A DOUBLE MAJOR IN
ART HISTORY AND BUSINESS ADMIN.

20:29.396 --> 20:31.698
THE PLAN IS TO BE
AN ENTREPRENEUR

20:31.731 --> 20:33.066
AND THEN A PHILANTHROPIST.

20:33.099 --> 20:34.901
SO,
YOU WANT TO BE RICH.

20:34.934 --> 20:36.836
FILTHY RICH, YEAH.

20:36.870 --> 20:38.938
WHEN I WAS YOUNGER,

20:38.972 --> 20:40.674
MY FAMILY DID THE WELFARE THING
FOR A COUPLE OF YEARS,

20:40.707 --> 20:43.910
AND I DECIDED
BROKE IS NOT FOR ME.

20:43.943 --> 20:46.079
SO, INDEPENDENT WOMAN.

20:46.112 --> 20:48.982
SEE, YOU ARE WHAT WE CALL
MULTIFACETED.

20:49.015 --> 20:51.418
AND I AM VERY HAPPY

20:51.451 --> 20:55.655
THAT I AM GETTING TO KNOW
THIS SIDE OF YOU.

20:55.689 --> 20:56.790
YEAH?

20:56.823 --> 20:58.058
YEAH.

20:58.091 --> 20:59.926
SO, HEY.
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

20:59.959 --> 21:02.362
WHAT'S THE OTHER SIDE
OF TERRENCE KING?

21:02.395 --> 21:04.330
WHAT'S YOUR
LONG-TERM PLAN?

21:04.364 --> 21:08.435
GET THE BLING AND THE RING.
WIN A CHAMPIONSHIP.

21:08.468 --> 21:10.870
BECOME A GLOBAL ICON.
YOU KNOW, THE USUAL.

21:10.904 --> 21:13.106
AND CONNOR'S GOT SOME
GREAT STUFF HE'S PITCHING ME

21:13.139 --> 21:15.408
THAT'S GONNA
MAKE THAT HAPPEN.
OKAY, WAIT.

21:15.442 --> 21:17.944
I MEAN,
YOU CAN'T LET THEM PITCH<i>YOU.</i>

21:17.977 --> 21:19.713
YOU'VE GOT TO PITCH<i>THEM.</i>

21:19.746 --> 21:22.716
MODELING AND FOOTBALL, THEY BOTH
HAVE A REALLY SHORT SHELF LIFE.

21:22.749 --> 21:25.085
YOU GOT TO MAXIMIZE
YOUR WINDOW OF OPPORTUNITY.

21:25.118 --> 21:28.955
SO, WHAT IS YOUR VISION?

21:30.990 --> 21:33.126
OKAY.

21:33.159 --> 21:36.996
MY VISION...
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

21:37.030 --> 21:38.631
...WOMEN'S PANTIES.

21:38.665 --> 21:41.935
[ LAUGHS ] PANTIES?
PANTIES ARE YOUR FUTURE?

21:41.968 --> 21:44.070
WELL, IT'S WEIRD WHEN YOU PUT IT
THAT WAY, BUT, YES.

21:44.104 --> 21:46.740
I WOULD START A LINGERIE LINE
CALLED BRICKHOUSE LINGERIE,

21:46.773 --> 21:48.775
FOR THAT WOMAN WHO'S BUILT LIKE
A '70s FUNK SONG.

21:48.808 --> 21:50.443
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?
[ LAUGHS ]

21:50.477 --> 21:52.479
[ LAUGHS ]
YOU HEARD OF A G-STRING?

21:52.512 --> 21:53.847
I HAVE.

21:53.880 --> 21:55.782
YEAH, WELL,
I WOULD MAKE A T.K.-STRING.

21:55.815 --> 21:56.850
YEAH, AND THEN I WOULD DO
SOME FLAVORED PANTIES

21:56.883 --> 21:59.652
FOR THE DISENFRANCHISED
YOUNG LADIES DOWN HERE,

21:59.686 --> 22:01.855
AND I WOULD PUT
SOME BOOTY PADS IN IT,

22:01.888 --> 22:03.923
'CAUSE YOU WANT THAT DONKY-DONK
IN THE TRUNKY-TRUNK

22:03.957 --> 22:05.658
WHEN YOU'RE MESSING
WITH THE BRICKHOUSE.

22:05.692 --> 22:07.794
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

22:07.827 --> 22:09.396
I THINK THAT T.K.
COULD BE FOR LINGERIE

22:09.429 --> 22:10.330
WHAT JOE NAMATH
WAS FOR PANTYHOSE.

22:10.363 --> 22:12.799
IT'S LIKE A MASCULINE TAKE
ON THE FEMININE.

22:12.832 --> 22:13.800
OKAY, I LOVE IT.

22:13.833 --> 22:15.135
Y-YOU DO?

22:15.168 --> 22:17.170
IT'S SEXY AND FUNNY
AND MASCULINE AND FEMININE.

22:17.203 --> 22:19.773
YOU ARE HITTING
ALL THE QUADRANTS.

22:19.806 --> 22:21.041
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT
I'M HITTING THEM QUADRANTS!

22:21.074 --> 22:21.875
THAT'S WHAT I DO!
I HIT QUADRANTS!

22:21.908 --> 22:23.943
[ LAUGHS ]
OKAY, I HAVE A CRAZY IDEA.

22:23.977 --> 22:26.413
WHAT IF YOU AND I
TEAMED UP?

22:26.446 --> 22:29.416
WE DID BRICKHOUSE TOGETHER.
HEAR ME OUT.

22:29.449 --> 22:32.886
WITH YOUR SWAG AND MY FASHION
SENSE AND MY CONNECTIONS,

22:32.919 --> 22:34.454
WE COULD BLOW
THIS THING UP LIKE...

22:34.487 --> 22:36.756
Both:
A KARDASHIAN DOING NOTHING.

22:36.790 --> 22:37.924
OKAY. WEIRD.

22:37.957 --> 22:39.726
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

22:42.128 --> 22:45.699
OOH!
PEONIES AND LILACS.

22:45.732 --> 22:47.033
PALOMA!
YES?

22:47.067 --> 22:48.768
OH. WHO GAVE ME THESE?

22:48.802 --> 22:51.137
A SECRET ADMIRER.
OPEN THE CARD.

22:51.171 --> 22:54.040
OH.

22:54.074 --> 22:58.044
"DINNER BEFORE I LEAVE TOWN?
DON'T TELL H.R."

22:58.078 --> 22:59.479
SAM.
OH, HE'S GOOD.

22:59.512 --> 23:01.781
WELL, HE'S PERSISTENT.
I'LL GIVE HIM THAT.

23:01.815 --> 23:04.017
WHO'S PERSISTENT?
NOBODY.

23:04.050 --> 23:05.785
NICE FLOWERS.
I KNOW.

23:05.819 --> 23:07.153
FROM SOMEBODY SPECIAL?
HEY!

23:07.187 --> 23:09.889
YEAH, FROM MR. NUNYA --
NUNYA BUSINESS.

23:09.923 --> 23:13.159
YOU HERE FOR A REASON OR YOU
JUST WANTED SOME OFFICE GOSSIP?

23:13.193 --> 23:14.994
NOT THE WATER-COOLER TYPE.

23:15.028 --> 23:16.996
COULD WE HAVE A MOMENT,
PRIVATELY?

23:17.030 --> 23:19.966
OH.
THANK YOU.

23:20.000 --> 23:22.002
SO...WHAT'S UP?

23:22.035 --> 23:24.471
POWERS PASSED
THE POLYGRAPH TEST.

23:24.504 --> 23:25.872
I ADMINISTERED IT
WITH AN EXPERT

23:25.905 --> 23:27.574
AND I THOUGHT THAT MIGHT
PUT YOUR MIND AT EASE.

23:27.607 --> 23:30.010
DOES CONNOR KNOW?
YES.

23:30.043 --> 23:32.178
CAN YOU PASS A POLYGRAPH
IF YOU'RE LYING?

23:32.212 --> 23:34.814
EXTREMELY DIFFICULT.

23:34.848 --> 23:36.783
CIA TRAINS GUYS TO DO IT,
BUT EVEN THEN.

23:36.816 --> 23:38.151
Paloma: DR. SANTINO.

23:38.184 --> 23:39.352
MM-HMM.
PHONE FOR YOU.

23:39.386 --> 23:41.187
WOULDN'T GIVE A NAME, BUT
IT SOUNDED LIKE NOLAN POWERS.

23:41.221 --> 23:42.989
OH.

23:44.624 --> 23:47.794
NOLAN?

23:47.827 --> 23:49.062
IS THAT YOU?

23:51.164 --> 23:52.599
WHAT DID HE SAY
EXACTLY?

23:52.632 --> 23:54.601
THAT HE WAS SCARED,
THAT HE WANTED TO TALK,

23:54.634 --> 23:56.803
AND TO MEET HIM AT THE HOTEL,
AND I'M TELLING YOU,

23:56.836 --> 24:00.006
IF NOLAN POWERS IS PLAYING
SOME ELABORATE MIND GAME,

24:00.040 --> 24:02.175
THEN I WANT A WITNESS
THIS TIME.

24:02.208 --> 24:06.146
[ BEEP ]
GEEZ. WHAT, DO YOU HAVE
AN ALL-POWERFUL KEY?

24:06.179 --> 24:08.014
NOLAN?

24:08.048 --> 24:10.083
NOLAN?

24:10.116 --> 24:12.619
[<i>CARTOON CHATTER</i>]

24:17.557 --> 24:20.126
OKAY.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

24:22.095 --> 24:24.197
HE'S NOT THERE.

24:24.230 --> 24:26.566
MR. POWERS!

24:30.103 --> 24:32.005
NOLAN!

24:43.583 --> 24:45.819
CREDIT CARDS,
DRIVER'S LICENSE --

24:45.852 --> 24:47.987
IT'S ODD TO LEAVE
THESE BEHIND.

24:48.021 --> 24:52.258
[ SIGHS ]
EVERYTHING ABOUT THIS IS ODD.

24:52.292 --> 24:53.993
WHAT IS A 40-YEAR-OLD MAN
DOING ALONE

24:54.027 --> 24:55.862
WATCHING CARTOONS,
PLAYING WITH STICKERS?

24:55.895 --> 24:58.231
UNLESS HE'S NOT ALONE.

24:58.264 --> 25:01.935
WE HAVE TO FIND HIM NOW,
NICO.

25:09.342 --> 25:10.010
*<i>SIT DOWN, CHILDREN</i>*

25:11.244 --> 25:12.412
Sheera: SO, TO WRAP IT UP,

25:12.445 --> 25:14.981
BRICKHOUSE WILL BE FUSING
THE MASCULINE WITH THE FEMININE

25:15.015 --> 25:18.151
IN A SYNERGY OF SEXY.

25:18.184 --> 25:22.789
SO, THAT'S IT. YEAH.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

25:22.822 --> 25:24.057
I THINK I LOVE MY JOB.

25:24.090 --> 25:25.759
[ LAUGHS ]

25:25.792 --> 25:28.661
HEY, T.K.
COME JOIN THE PARTY.

25:28.695 --> 25:30.163
WHAT KIND OF PARTY IS THIS,
EXACTLY?

25:30.196 --> 25:32.966
SHEERA WAS JUST TELLING ME
ABOUT THE IDEA YOU GUYS HAD.

25:32.999 --> 25:34.167
BRICKHOUSE LINGERIE.
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

25:34.200 --> 25:37.904
PAUSE.

25:37.937 --> 25:40.173
*<i>THAT DUDE</i>*

25:40.206 --> 25:42.742
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

25:42.776 --> 25:45.979
I THOUGHT THAT WE DISCUSSED
PITCHING MY IDEA TO CONNOR

25:46.012 --> 25:47.847
WHEN THE TIME
WAS APPROPRIATE?

25:47.881 --> 25:49.049
AND I THOUGHT
THE APPROPRIATE TIME WOULD BE

25:49.082 --> 25:51.017
WHEN I WAS ACTUALLY HERE
TO PITCH IT?

25:51.051 --> 25:53.019
T.K., THIS IS NOT WHAT
IT LOOKS LIKE, SO YOU
NEED TO LET ME EXPLAIN.

25:53.053 --> 25:54.287
WHAT KIND OF GAMES
ARE YOU PLAYING?

25:54.320 --> 25:56.022
I AM NOT
PLAYING ANY GAMES.

25:56.056 --> 25:57.824
IT LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE PLAYING
LINGERIE FOOTBALL.

25:57.857 --> 25:59.259
OKAY, STOP.
CAN WE TALK ABOUT THIS LATER?

25:59.292 --> 26:01.094
BECAUSE YOU ARE BEING
UNPROFESSIONAL.

26:01.127 --> 26:02.228
<i>I'M</i>BEING UNPROFESSIONAL?
YEAH.

26:02.262 --> 26:03.063
YOU NEED TO LOOK
IN THE MIRROR,

26:03.096 --> 26:05.198
BECAUSE THE REFLECTION
HAS TWO SIDES.

26:05.231 --> 26:07.734
YOU KNOW WHAT?
NEVER MIND.

26:07.767 --> 26:09.836
CONNOR, BRICKHOUSE LINGERIE
WAS MY IDEA FIRST.

26:09.869 --> 26:11.938
YES.
SO SHE HAS NO RIGHT
TO PITCH THIS TO YOU

26:11.971 --> 26:13.273
WITHOUT MY CONSENT.

26:13.306 --> 26:14.808
ALL RIGHT,
THERE SEEMS TO BE

26:14.841 --> 26:16.209
SOME SORT OF
COMMUNICATION GLITCH HERE,

26:16.242 --> 26:17.944
AND I SUGGEST
YOU BOTH FIGURE OUT,

26:17.977 --> 26:19.813
BECAUSE WE'RE ONE BIG,
HAPPY FAMILY.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

26:19.846 --> 26:21.281
SHE AND I ARE NOT
ON THE SAME FAMILY HERE, OKAY?

26:21.314 --> 26:23.016
AND AS MY FIRST
ORDER OF BUSINESS

26:23.049 --> 26:25.985
AS THE C.E.O. OF BRICKHOUSE,
SHEERA, YOU'RE FIRED.

26:26.953 --> 26:30.023
NO, NO. TAKE YOUR BRICKS
UP OUT OF MY HOUSE.

26:30.056 --> 26:31.958
T.K, COME -- T.K.!

26:31.991 --> 26:34.027
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

26:34.060 --> 26:35.895
Nico: WE WENT THROUGH
THE SURVEILLANCE TAPES.

26:35.929 --> 26:38.998
POWERS WAS THE ONLY ONE WHO WENT
IN AND OUT OF THE ROOM,

26:39.032 --> 26:41.968
AND HE ARRIVED AT AND LEFT
THE HOTEL BY HIMSELF -- NO KIDS.

26:42.002 --> 26:46.272
SO [SIGHS]
WHAT ARE WE MISSING?

27:04.024 --> 27:05.125
[ SIGHS ]

27:07.027 --> 27:08.762
Connor: IMITREX.

27:08.795 --> 27:10.230
MM-HMM.
IT'S USED FOR MIGRAINES.

27:10.263 --> 27:11.498
OH, YEAH.
HE'S HAD THOSE FOR YEARS.

27:11.531 --> 27:13.800
AND HE BLACKS OUT SOMETIMES.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"BLACKS OUT"?

27:13.833 --> 27:15.068
I DON'T KNOW.
HE JUST BLACKS OUT.

27:15.101 --> 27:16.369
I MEAN, THAT'S WHY
HE DOESN'T DRINK.

27:16.403 --> 27:18.371
HE DOESN'T
WANT TO LOSE CONTROL.

27:18.405 --> 27:21.775
ALL RIGHT, SO, ALLIE SAID
HE CUT OFF CONTACT.

27:21.808 --> 27:23.877
WE HAVE HIS CELLPHONE,
AND HE'S NOT AT THE HOTEL.

27:23.910 --> 27:26.146
YEAH, AND NICO CHECKED
THE HOSPITALS, THE MORGUE.
HOW DOES THIS HAPPEN?

27:26.179 --> 27:29.049
HOW DOES A RECOGNIZABLE GUY
LIKE POWERS JUST DISAPPEAR

27:29.082 --> 27:30.016
INTO THIN AIR?

27:30.050 --> 27:31.785
AND THIS STUFF --
THIS DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.

27:31.818 --> 27:35.889
I MEAN, DRAWINGS, CRAYONS,
KID SCISSORS.

27:35.922 --> 27:37.290
YEAH,
THEY'RE LEFTY SCISSORS.

27:37.323 --> 27:38.925
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
LEFTY SCISSORS?

27:38.958 --> 27:40.860
LEFTY.

27:44.798 --> 27:46.900
GOOD NEWS AND BAD NEWS.

27:46.933 --> 27:48.234
WE THINK WE FOUND HIM.
W-WHERE?

27:48.268 --> 27:49.836
THE TRENTON POLICE
ARE HOLDING HIM

27:49.869 --> 27:52.372
FOR ATTEMPTED ARSON
OF HIS CHILDHOOD HOME.

27:52.405 --> 27:54.941
HE HAD NO I.D. ON HIM.
HE WAS DISORIENTED.

27:54.974 --> 27:56.176
A COP BUDDY
WHO OWES ME A FAVOR

27:56.209 --> 27:57.944
IS KEEPING A LID ON IT
UNTIL WE GET OUT THERE.

27:57.977 --> 28:01.214
[ SIGHS ]
JASMINE? JASMINE.
Jasmine: YEAH?

28:01.247 --> 28:03.283
CALL BEN AND HAVE HIM FIRE UP
THE HELICOPTER.

28:03.316 --> 28:04.517
WE'RE GOING TO TRENTON.
YOU GOT IT.

28:04.551 --> 28:07.153
WHY DOES A GUY LIKE NOLAN POWERS
TRY TO BURN HIS HOUSE DOWN?

28:07.187 --> 28:08.421
OR WHY -- WHY DOES HE DO
ANY OF THIS?

28:10.924 --> 28:13.426
UNLESS IT'S NOT
NOLAN POWERS.

28:16.129 --> 28:18.932
[ SIREN WAILS ]

28:18.965 --> 28:21.134
I OWE YOU.

28:21.167 --> 28:22.268
ALL SMOOTHED OUT.

28:22.302 --> 28:25.338
NO CHARGES WILL BE FILED.
HE'S IN THE HOLDING AREA.

28:25.372 --> 28:27.841
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
BEFORE THEY RELEASE HIM
AND HE RUNS OFF AGAIN,

28:27.874 --> 28:30.076
I WOULD REALLY
LIKE TO SPEAK WITH HIM.
YEAH, SO WOULD I.

28:30.110 --> 28:33.246
WELL, WOULD YOU MIND
IF I TALKED TO HIM FIRST, ALONE?

28:36.016 --> 28:38.051
JEFF.

28:38.084 --> 28:40.887
[ SIGHS ]

28:40.920 --> 28:42.288
[ SIGHS ]

28:42.322 --> 28:45.158
I DIDN'T SET
SOME HOUSE ON FIRE.

28:45.191 --> 28:47.394
OKAY, BUT IT WASN'T
JUST<i>SOME</i>HOUSE.

28:47.427 --> 28:49.029
IT'S WHERE YOU GREW UP,
RIGHT?

28:49.062 --> 28:51.031
SO WHAT?!
I WASN'T TRYING TO BURN IT DOWN!

28:51.064 --> 28:54.401
WHAT<i>WERE</i>YOU DOING THERE,
NOLAN?

28:54.434 --> 28:56.970
I DON'T KNOW.

28:57.003 --> 28:59.406
[ SIGHS ]

29:06.312 --> 29:08.014
NOLAN, WHO WROTE THIS?

29:08.048 --> 29:09.983
NOT ME!

29:10.016 --> 29:11.484
SOMEONE'S TRYING TO DESTROY ME!
DON'T YOU GET IT?!

29:11.518 --> 29:13.420
WHO? WHO IS TRYING
TO DESTROY YOU?

29:13.453 --> 29:15.288
HELP ME UNDERSTAND THAT.

29:15.321 --> 29:16.389
OH, GOD.

29:16.423 --> 29:19.092
ARE YOU HAVING
ANOTHER MIGRAINE?

29:19.125 --> 29:21.327
I'M NOT GONNA TALK TO ANYONE
UNTIL I SEE MY LAWYER.

29:21.361 --> 29:23.063
OKAY. OKAY.

29:23.096 --> 29:27.000
I UNDERSTAND.
YOU DON'T WANT TO TALK TO ME.

29:27.033 --> 29:28.368
I'M JUST WONDERING...

29:28.401 --> 29:31.971
IF SOMEONE ELSE DOES.

29:32.005 --> 29:34.040
SOMEONE ELSE? WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

30:03.236 --> 30:05.338
WHAT ARE YOU DRAWING?

30:05.372 --> 30:07.173
CASTLE.

30:07.207 --> 30:09.109
IT KEEPS PEOPLE SAFE.

30:10.944 --> 30:13.179
I WANT TO
TELL YOU SOMETHING

30:13.213 --> 30:15.348
ABOUT WHAT'S BEEN GOING ON,
BUT HE WON'T LISTEN.

30:16.950 --> 30:20.053
WELL,<i>I'LL</i>LISTEN.

30:20.086 --> 30:21.187
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

30:21.221 --> 30:22.222
SCOTTY.

30:27.227 --> 30:29.029
HOW OLD ARE YOU,
SCOTTY?

30:29.062 --> 30:30.263
8 3/4.

30:35.235 --> 30:37.170
IT'S ALL GOOD.

30:37.203 --> 30:39.172
WE SHOULD GET HIM OUT OF HERE
BEFORE ANYBODY SNIFFS THIS OUT.

30:39.205 --> 30:40.240
OKAY.

30:43.443 --> 30:45.578
YOU OKAY?
WHAT HAPPENED IN THERE?

30:45.612 --> 30:48.081
UM...

30:48.114 --> 30:51.117
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE TO BEGIN.

30:56.389 --> 30:56.856
MULTIPLE PERSONALITIES?

30:57.891 --> 31:00.927
IT'S ALSO CALLED
DISSOCIATIVE IDENTITY DISORDER.

31:00.960 --> 31:04.397
IT'S WHEN TWO DISTINCT
IDENTITIES ARE FIGHTING

31:04.431 --> 31:06.266
TO CONTROL ONE PERSON.

31:06.299 --> 31:09.269
AND OFTEN,
MEMORY LOSS ACCOMPANIES IT.

31:09.302 --> 31:12.005
SO, YOU'RE SAYING
THESE BLACKOUTS

31:12.038 --> 31:14.941
ARE 'CAUSE THIS ALTER EGO,
SCOTTY,

31:14.974 --> 31:17.077
HAS TAKEN CONTROL
OF MY MIND?

31:17.110 --> 31:20.347
SOMEWHERE IN YOUR CHILDHOOD,
YOU SUFFERED ABUSE

31:20.380 --> 31:22.349
THAT WAS SO TRAUMATIZING --

31:22.382 --> 31:25.418
SEVERE ENOUGH
THAT IT FORCED YOU TO SPLIT,

31:25.452 --> 31:27.087
TO DISASSOCIATE.

31:27.120 --> 31:29.356
YOU ARE
THE HOST PERSONALITY

31:29.389 --> 31:32.726
THAT HAS CREATED
THIS ENTIRE EMPIRE.

31:32.759 --> 31:35.161
AND THEN SCOTTY,
THE ALTER PERSONALITY,

31:35.195 --> 31:38.231
IS THIS SCARED 8-YEAR-OLD,
LITTLE BOY.

31:38.264 --> 31:40.700
THE ONE WHO SENT
THOSE E-MAILS.

31:40.734 --> 31:42.702
THE ONE WHO WANTS HELP.

31:42.736 --> 31:45.005
BUT HOW CAN I POSSIBLY
HAVE BUILT WHAT I'VE BUILT

31:45.038 --> 31:47.374
IF I REALLY HAVE
THIS ALTER EGO?

31:47.407 --> 31:51.211
MANY PEOPLE WITH D.I.D. ARE
EXCEPTIONALLY HIGH FUNCTIONING.

31:51.244 --> 31:53.747
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
HEISMAN TROPHY WINNERS, C.E.O.s,

31:53.780 --> 31:55.749
FAMOUS MUSICIANS
AND ACTORS.

31:55.782 --> 32:00.320
AND, FRANKLY, THEIR ABILITY
TO COMPARTMENTALIZE

32:00.353 --> 32:02.055
IS A BIG PART
OF THEIR SUCCESS.

32:06.393 --> 32:10.196
SO...WHAT NOW?

32:10.230 --> 32:13.133
WELL, I WOULD LIKE TO REFER YOU
TO A SPECIALIST

32:13.166 --> 32:15.301
WHO DEALS WITH
THIS CONDITION,

32:15.335 --> 32:18.171
'CAUSE IT'S OUT OF
MY AREA OF EXPERTISE.

32:18.204 --> 32:21.174
BUT I DO KNOW ONE THING,
AND THAT IS IF YOU WANT TO

32:21.207 --> 32:26.279
INTEGRATE SCOTTY AND NOLAN,
THEN THERAPY IS IMPERATIVE.

32:26.312 --> 32:29.716
AND, UH...

32:29.749 --> 32:32.152
AND WHAT IF I DON'T GO?

32:32.185 --> 32:36.189
SCOTTY WILL KEEP TRYING
TO BURN THE HOUSE DOWN

32:36.222 --> 32:38.291
UNTIL HE IS HEARD.

32:38.324 --> 32:44.297
AND YOU WILL HAVE
MANY MORE EPISODES LIKE THESE.

32:44.330 --> 32:46.700
[ SIGHS ]

32:46.733 --> 32:49.169
HOW THE HELL
DID YOU FIGURE ALL THIS OUT?

32:49.202 --> 32:52.706
IT WAS THE SUDDEN SHIFT IN
PERSONALITIES AND THE MIGRAINES,

32:52.739 --> 32:54.307
THE BLACKOUTS
THAT YOU MENTIONED.

32:54.341 --> 32:58.044
IT'S HOW HE TRANSITIONED
BETWEEN PERSONAS.

32:58.078 --> 33:00.046
SO HE WAS EITHER
A PATHOLOGICAL LIAR

33:00.080 --> 33:02.182
OR HE REALLY DIDN'T REMEMBER
DOING THOSE THINGS.

33:02.215 --> 33:04.284
SO, THAT'S HOW HE PASSED
THE LIE-DETECTOR TEST?

33:04.317 --> 33:05.452
YES.

33:05.485 --> 33:07.320
I ALSO PICKED UP
THAT HE SWITCHED

33:07.354 --> 33:09.489
FROM BEING A RIGHTY
TO A LEFTY,

33:09.522 --> 33:12.258
WHICH IS ANOTHER SIGN
OF SWITCHING PERSONAS.

33:12.292 --> 33:16.830
I THINK THAT HE RESISTED
GOING TO THERAPY ALL THESE YEARS

33:16.863 --> 33:17.797
IN AN EFFORT TO HIDE IT.

33:17.831 --> 33:20.266
MM-HMM.
RIGHT?
'CAUSE SCOTTY WANTED HELP.

33:20.300 --> 33:23.403
BUT THEN POWERS
WANTED TO HIDE THE TRUTH,

33:23.436 --> 33:26.406
SO THEN HE JUST TAUGHT HIMSELF
TO SNAP OUT OF IT.

33:26.439 --> 33:29.275
THINKING ABOUT THIS THING
IS GIVING<i>ME</i>A MIGRAINE.

33:29.309 --> 33:31.745
I KNOW.
HE DIDN'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT.

33:31.778 --> 33:34.080
THAT'S WHY HE WANTED ME
TO EXPLAIN IT TO YOU.

33:34.114 --> 33:38.218
BUT HE DID WANT YOU TO KNOW THAT
HE WILL BE AT THE BOOK SIGNING.

33:38.251 --> 33:40.220
HEY, SANTINO.

33:40.253 --> 33:43.156
I'M SORRY THAT I DIDN'T,
UH, TRUST YOU.

33:43.189 --> 33:47.260
IT'S A NEW RELATIONSHIP.
TRUST IS EARNED.

33:47.293 --> 33:49.362
ALL RIGHT. HERE.

33:49.396 --> 33:51.431
ENJOY.

33:58.405 --> 33:59.339
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

33:59.372 --> 34:02.108
[ MUMBLING ]

34:02.142 --> 34:05.111
HEY, CONNOR, I JUST WANTED
TO SAY I WAS SORRY ABOUT --

34:05.145 --> 34:07.380
SAVE IT.
NO NEED FOR SORRY. I'M IN.

34:07.414 --> 34:09.783
[ LAUGHS ]
THAT'S -- THAT'S GREAT.

34:09.816 --> 34:13.119
UH, BUT, UH,
YOU'RE IN FOR WHAT EXACTLY?

34:13.153 --> 34:15.121
BRICKHOUSE.

34:15.155 --> 34:16.156
HI.

34:16.189 --> 34:17.190
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:17.223 --> 34:18.625
Connor: I'VE HAD SOME TIME
TO THINK ABOUT THIS.

34:18.658 --> 34:21.261
THIS IS -- THIS IS GOOD.
THIS IS DYNAMIC.

34:21.294 --> 34:23.396
I MEAN, THE MERGING
OF YOUR TWO DIFFERENT PERSONAS

34:23.430 --> 34:25.165
IS LIKE YIN AND YANG.

34:25.198 --> 34:26.633
LIKE WE'RE TWO SIDES
OF THE SAME COIN.

34:26.666 --> 34:29.202
A SEXY COIN, THOUGH, SO YOU TWO
NEED TO KISS AND MAKE UP.

34:29.235 --> 34:32.339
YES. I MEAN, THINK ABOUT IT.
THE TWO OF YOU TOGETHER,
PIMPING THIS THING OUT?

34:32.372 --> 34:34.474
AND BRICKHOUSE COULD DO
FOR LINGERIE

34:34.507 --> 34:36.209
WHAT P. DIDDY DID
FOR MEN'S WEAR.

34:37.577 --> 34:40.280
YOU THINK SO?

34:40.313 --> 34:42.215
I KNOW SO.
WE JUST HAVE TO COME UP

34:42.248 --> 34:43.116
WITH A BRAND NAME
LIKE HE DID --

34:43.149 --> 34:44.617
LIKE SEAN JOHN,
SO LET'S THINK ABOUT IT.

34:44.651 --> 34:46.820
WE GOT, UH --
OH, T.K, SHEERA.

34:46.853 --> 34:47.821
TKEERA.
[ FINGERS SNAP ]

34:47.854 --> 34:49.422
SHE-K.
I LOVE IT.

34:49.456 --> 34:51.358
WHY DOES SHE GET
TOP BILLING?
THIS IS GOOD.

34:51.391 --> 34:53.226
WE'LL PUT A DESIGN TEAM
TOGETHER.

34:53.259 --> 34:55.195
"BRICKHOUSE BY SHE-K."
I LIKE THIS.

34:55.228 --> 34:57.564
I HOPE YOU TWO
LIKE WORKING TOGETHER,

34:57.597 --> 34:59.165
BECAUSE THIS IS --
THIS IS GOOD.

34:59.199 --> 35:01.368
POWERS --
ON THE PHONE.

35:01.401 --> 35:02.602
ALL RIGHT. YOU TWO -- DA-DA.
[ FINGERS SNAP ]

35:12.545 --> 35:14.547
HONEY, I'M HOME.

35:14.581 --> 35:16.282
WHAT'S FOR DINNER?

35:16.316 --> 35:19.652
I [LAUGHS] UH, SLEEP
WITH A SIDE OF SLEEP.

35:19.686 --> 35:20.653
I'M HEADING OUT.

35:20.687 --> 35:22.355
I SEE YOU GO THE FLOWERS.

35:22.389 --> 35:24.924
OH, MY GOD.
YES. THANK YOU.

35:24.958 --> 35:26.893
I'M SO SORRY.
THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.

35:26.926 --> 35:28.595
TOUGH DAY?

35:28.628 --> 35:31.264
TOUGH WEEK.

35:31.297 --> 35:32.165
I GOT JUST THE CURE.

35:32.198 --> 35:34.234
I'M STAYING AT
THE EMPIRE GRAND HOTEL.

35:34.267 --> 35:36.403
THE BARTENDER THERE
MAKES A MARTINI

35:36.436 --> 35:38.605
YOU COULD PRESCRIBE
TO KILL DEPRESSION.

35:38.638 --> 35:40.273
JOIN ME
FOR SOME TREATMENT?

35:40.306 --> 35:43.877
OH, I'M NOT SURE
THAT'S SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

35:43.910 --> 35:45.612
FAIR ENOUGH.

35:45.645 --> 35:47.881
BUT IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND,
I'LL BE THERE.

35:47.914 --> 35:50.350
TONIGHT, TOMORROW NIGHT --
LADY'S CHOICE.

35:50.383 --> 35:53.286
COULD BE YOU JUST NEED A LITTLE
OF MY PERSONAL THERAPY.

35:53.319 --> 35:55.388
OH.

36:00.360 --> 36:03.897
OH, WELL,
BACK TO THAT EMPTY CALENDAR.

36:03.930 --> 36:05.732
OH, HI, PIMPY.
ASSIST-Y.

36:05.765 --> 36:07.500
I'M JUST WONDERING
WHAT'S STOPPING YOU,

36:07.534 --> 36:10.403
AN UNATTACHED, AWESOME WOMAN,
FROM HAVING DRINKS

36:10.437 --> 36:13.473
WITH AN UNATTACHED,
HANDSOME, LOVELY MAN?

36:23.483 --> 36:26.353
EVERYTHING
YOU ASKED FOR.

36:26.386 --> 36:29.022
SAYS HE FOUND A SECOND SET
OF BOOKS V3 KEEPS.

36:29.055 --> 36:30.957
ALL ITS FINANCIAL
TRANSACTIONS.

36:30.990 --> 36:34.561
OH, THIS IS
DISNEYLAND-WORTHY.

36:34.594 --> 36:37.430
OUR ANALYSTS
WILL HAVE A FIELD DAY.

36:37.464 --> 36:40.300
OUTSTANDING, MR. CARELES.

36:40.333 --> 36:42.969
NOW,
ABOUT THAT DOWN PAYMENT.

36:43.003 --> 36:46.306
WHAT DID YOU
HAVE IN MIND?

36:46.339 --> 36:47.974
I.C.E.

36:48.008 --> 36:50.310
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

36:50.343 --> 36:52.946
Man: THIS IS I.C.E.
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

36:56.816 --> 37:01.554
WHAT'S
YOUR BUSINESS HERE?

37:01.588 --> 37:04.290
VISITATION.

37:04.324 --> 37:06.426
I.D.?

37:09.662 --> 37:12.632
YOU MUST HAVE SOME FRIENDS
IN HIGH PLACES.

37:12.665 --> 37:14.034
NAME OF THE INMATE?

37:14.067 --> 37:17.003
CARELES.
ALEX CARELES.

37:19.839 --> 37:22.809
TO YOUR LEFT.

37:22.842 --> 37:24.044
THANKS.

37:24.077 --> 37:26.312
[ BUZZER ]

37:34.621 --> 37:36.489
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

37:39.492 --> 37:40.660
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
MARK.

37:40.694 --> 37:43.463
MARK? NICE TO MEET YOU, MARK.
THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR COMING.

37:43.496 --> 37:44.464
HEY.
HEY.

37:44.497 --> 37:46.700
I SPOKE TO POWERS.
AND...?

37:46.733 --> 37:49.102
AND HE'S BLOWING OFF
THE PSYCHIATRIST YOU
WANTED HIM TO SEE.

37:49.135 --> 37:50.670
CONNOR,
YOU CAN'T LET HIM DO THAT.

37:50.704 --> 37:52.472
HE NEEDS HELP.

37:52.505 --> 37:55.709
HE'S A TICKING TIME BOMB,
AND WHEN HE GOES BOOM --

37:55.742 --> 37:58.345
HE'LL WRITE ANOTHER BOOK
ALL ABOUT IT,

37:58.378 --> 38:00.580
HE'LL MAKE ANOTHER $100 MILLION,
AND I'LL DO WHAT I ALWAYS DO.

38:00.613 --> 38:01.681
I'LL KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.

38:01.715 --> 38:04.384
SANTINO,
DON'T TAKE THIS SO HARD.

38:04.417 --> 38:05.385
YOU DID YOUR BEST.

38:31.678 --> 38:33.613
THIS IS FOR YOU, MISS.

38:34.681 --> 38:37.684
MY GOD.

38:44.691 --> 38:45.658
WOW.

38:45.692 --> 38:47.694
YEAH.

38:52.766 --> 38:53.299
Dani: [ LAUGHS ]
NOW, SEE?

38:54.334 --> 38:55.235
YOU JUST NEEDED
A LITTLE LAUGHTER IN YOUR LIFE.

38:55.268 --> 38:57.404
MM-HMM.
I'M GLAD
YOU CHANGED YOUR MIND.

38:57.437 --> 38:58.571
ME TOO.

38:58.605 --> 39:00.840
CAN'T FORGET
THAT EVERY NOW AND THEN

39:00.874 --> 39:02.409
YOU NEED TO...DECOMPRESS.

39:02.442 --> 39:05.578
AND YOU WERE RIGHT.
THESE MARTINIS ARE AWESOME.

39:05.612 --> 39:08.915
MY BEST FRIEND FELL IN LOVE
OVER ONE OF THESE.

39:08.948 --> 39:10.050
OH?

39:10.083 --> 39:11.451
I CAN SEE HOW.

39:11.484 --> 39:14.120
[ SIGHS ]
Bartender: LAST CALL.

39:14.154 --> 39:16.122
COULD YOU JUST PUT IT
ON THE ROOM?
OF COURSE.

39:16.156 --> 39:18.091
THANK YOU.
OHH.

39:18.124 --> 39:19.959
LOOKS LIKE THE PARTY'S
COMING TO AN END.

39:19.993 --> 39:23.530
HMM...
MAYBE IT DOESN'T HAVE TO.

39:23.563 --> 39:25.965
OH. [ LAUGHS ]

39:25.999 --> 39:28.935
WELL, I DON'T KNOW IF I'VE HAD
<i>THAT</i>MANY MARTINIS.

39:28.968 --> 39:30.937
MAYBE I'M NOT
THAT KIND OF GIRL.

39:30.970 --> 39:33.173
WELL, MAYBE DR. SANTINO
FROM THE OFFICE ISN'T.

39:33.206 --> 39:36.209
BUT THE DANI
SITTING RIGHT HERE --

39:36.242 --> 39:38.611
SHE MIGHT BE
A DIFFERENT STORY.

39:38.645 --> 39:42.515
SHE SEEMS TO ENJOY A FUN TIME,
AND THAT IS WHAT I'M PROMISING.

39:44.684 --> 39:47.053
I LEAVE TOMORROW.

39:47.087 --> 39:50.657
BUT TONIGHT,
I'M IN ROOM 314.

39:52.926 --> 39:55.528
OH, AND...

39:55.562 --> 39:59.632
IF THE OFF CHANCE
I'M WRONG ABOUT THIS,

39:59.666 --> 40:02.102
PLEASE DON'T TELL H.R.

40:02.135 --> 40:03.536
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

40:08.541 --> 40:10.076
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

40:15.215 --> 40:19.519
* BABY,
DON'T YOU WORRY ABOUT ME *

40:19.552 --> 40:22.989
* 'CAUSE I MIGHT BE AWHILE

40:23.023 --> 40:26.259
* I'M JUST TAKING MY TIME

40:26.292 --> 40:30.096
* WIPE THE STARS
FROM YOUR EYES NOW, BABY *

40:30.130 --> 40:33.733
* YOUR EYES NOW, BABY

40:33.767 --> 40:37.704
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
* I'M JUST WASTING
YOUR TIME, BABY *

40:37.737 --> 40:41.074
* DON'T YOU WORRY ABOUT ME

40:41.107 --> 40:45.612
* YOU'LL REALIZE REAL GUYS
LEARN HOW TO SEE *

40:45.645 --> 40:48.648
* THAT I'M

40:48.682 --> 40:52.719
* I'M JUST FIGURING IT OUT

40:52.752 --> 40:55.522
HEY.
HEY.

40:55.555 --> 40:57.991
* YEAH,
I'M JUST FIGURING IT OUT *
WHAT'S UP? UH...

40:58.024 --> 41:00.160
IN ANOTHER TIME,

41:00.193 --> 41:02.796
I-I-I-I WOULD HAVE
TAKEN YOU UP ON THIS,

41:02.829 --> 41:07.534
BUT, UM, IT'S BEEN
A REALLY...ROUGH YEAR,

41:07.567 --> 41:09.669
SO I JUST, YOU KNOW --
BUT, UH --

41:09.703 --> 41:10.804
JUST -- HERE YOU GO.

41:14.741 --> 41:18.244
* BABY,
DON'T YOU WAIT UP FOR ME *
LET ME MAKE IT BETTER.

41:18.278 --> 41:21.247
* 'CAUSE I'M ALL ON MY OWN

41:21.281 --> 41:25.051
* AND, BABY, TWO'S A CROWD

41:25.085 --> 41:29.055
* MOVE YOUR HEAD
FROM THE CLOUDS NOW, BABY *

41:29.089 --> 41:32.058
* 'CAUSE I CAN'T HEAR YOU

41:32.092 --> 41:35.762
* THE MOVIE'S WAY TOO LOUD

41:35.795 --> 41:40.066
* BABY,
DON'T YOU WORRY ABOUT ME *

41:40.100 --> 41:44.738
* YOU'LL REALIZE REAL GUYS
LEARN HOW TO SEE *

41:44.771 --> 41:48.041
* THAT I'M

41:48.074 --> 41:52.145
* I'M JUST FIGURING IT OUT

41:52.178 --> 41:57.217
* YEAH,
I'M JUST FIGURING IT OUT *
